      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "JUNK YARD LORAIN (1) had to overcome a collision with another runner and could manage only a distant seventh (17.94) in a Grade 6 over 300m at this track. Better than latest and worth another try. LEVI BLAZER (8) should get a clear run from the wide draw. Safely held last start when a 6 length 6th at this track (17.80). Goes very well at course and distance boasting one wins. Solid formlines coming through his last run. Worth following up. SILLY OLD BEAR (2) finds it hard to win. Finished third (17.79) at this track latest and might be close to finding winning form again. The form out of the last run is proven to be strong. Can feature again. LET'S GO SPIKE (7) should bounce back after an unplaced effort here recently.",
